OL,3,CReeves faces Budget 'groundhog day'
OL,4,Cwithout bold action, says IFS
OL,6,FThat figure would restore the #10
OL,7,Fbillion of headroom Ms Reeves
OL,8,Fpreviously left herself against her
OL,9,Fself-imposed debt rules, although it
OL,10,Fdoes not include the cost of widely
OL,11,Fexpected announcements on abolishing
OL,12,Fthe two-child benefit cap and
OL,13,Fmaintaining the freeze on fuel duty.
OL,15,FBut the IFS said there was a "strong
OL,16,Fcase" for the Chancellor to go
OL,17,Ffurther, arguing that a #10 billion
OL,18,Fbuffer was not enough to ensure
OL,19,Fstability and would leave her "limping
OL,20,Ffrom one forecast to the next".
