OL,3,CReeves faces Budget 'groundhog day'
OL,4,Cwithout bold action, says IFS
OL,6,FMs Miller suggested it would be
OL,7,Fpossible to raise the required sums
OL,8,Ffrom changes to property taxes and
OL,9,Flevies such as capital gains tax or
OL,10,Finheritance tax, but added these were
OL,11,F"badly designed" and could harm growth.
OL,13,FThe IFS also warned against seeking
OL,14,F"large sums from a small number of
OL,15,Ftaxpayers".
OL,17,FInstead, the think tank said the
OL,18,FChancellor "should be bold" and reform
OL,19,Fthe tax system to be "more rational"
OL,20,Fand impinge less on economic growth.
