OL,3,CReeves faces Budget 'groundhog day'
OL,4,Cwithout bold action, says IFS
OL,6,FJack Meaning, chief UK economist at
OL,7,FBarclays, said: "With the right policy
OL,8,Fdecisions, this near-term challenge
OL,9,Fcan be navigated toward a more
OL,10,Ffavourable medium-term outlook.
OL,12,F"If the Chancellor can avoid
OL,13,Fdelivering an inflationary Budget,
OL,14,Fheadline price growth should ease
OL,15,Fsignificantly in the coming months,
OL,16,Fallowing the Bank of England to cut
OL,17,Finterest rates further and support
OL,18,Fhouseholds and businesses in driving
OL,19,Fmore balanced economic growth."
